{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/60/comments/60801438.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake:61847d89595c..c5f1c35a73f6?path=cmake%2FIgnCodeCheck.cmake"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/60/_/diff#comment-60801438"}}, "parent": {"id": 60800831, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/60/comments/60800831.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/60/_/diff#comment-60800831"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Adding cppcheck and cpplint with codecheck target"}, "content": {"raw": "Inside of `IgnConfigureBuild.cmake`, you can find the logic for parsing the components and identifying which components are available. I would suggest putting something in the `ign_configure_build(~)` function to append entries for the components to the `CPPCHECK_DIRS` list.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Inside of <code>IgnConfigureBuild.cmake</code>, you can find the logic for parsing the components and identifying which components are available. I would suggest putting something in the <code>ign_configure_build(~)</code> function to append entries for the components to the <code>CPPCHECK_DIRS</code> list.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-05T18:23:03.403830+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.p